=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_LFPulse_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark mixed sound, with square_like oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring punchy attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: mixed
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -9.4070
  harmonic_regularity: 0.8111
  pitch_clarity: 10.3619
  inharmonicity: 0.5295
  type: square_like
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -14.1156
  resonance_freq: 430.6641

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: LFPulse Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/LFPulse.html
// Tags: LFPulse, Classes, oscillator, modulation
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
{ LFPulse.kr(XLine.kr(1, 200, 10), 0, 0.2) * SinOsc.ar(440) * 0.1 }.play;
